It's time for Gabi to leave the Limbo.

Where is this Misfit going?

It's just Sergio trying to give her mouth-to-mouth, but it's close enough. "I'm doing great," she's thinking.

There could be worse ways to die.

THE END.
or is it? >>
Now, choking on a chocolate raisin on the kitchen floor, surrounded by 12 people shouting "somebody get help!" at each other, she finally gets her final kiss from the man she loves.>>

After one too many drinks, or maybe three too many, she decides to go talk to Sergio. Maybe it's her last chance. She's trying to find an ice breaker, something to impress him. He is the kind of guy that always looks like he just came out of the shower, even when he didn't.>>

On her sister's 29th birthday, in her small patio apartment, Gabi is standing with her back against the wall, putting on her best fake smile. She doesn‚Äôt want to ruin a good birthday party.

She will.>>

The only guy she truly likes is Sergio. He's very funny and smells great and his shirts are always ketchup-free, and he happens to be engaged to her younger sister. Because sometimes life just ain't fair. They won't tell you that in those affirmation tapes.>>

It was a very quiet flight back to Spain. Sometimes she thinks they might get back together.

They won't.>>

Her desktop picture is a photo she took five years ago on her trip to a Greek island. She couldn't even pronounce its name, "Zhakintis" or something like that. A day after she took that picture, she broke up with her boyfriend.>>

and not give a tip to the waitress because "she's doing her job; why should I give her extra money?"

It never worked out for Gabi, now almost 32.>>

The only one doing great and being successful is the guy who made those tapes.
Sometimes her mom tries to set her up with some random guy. "He's the son of Rita from work; he's a doctor!" Well, it turns out even doctors can come to a date with a ketchup stain on their shirt >>

Every night, before she goes to bed, Gabi puts on her AirPods and listens to a track on YouTube called "Positive Affirmation  s." She repeats the lines. "You are beautiful. You are successful. You are doing great" It's supposed to make her feel better.

It doesn't. >>

Gabriella "Gabi" Martinez
1990‚Äì2022

In her senior yearbook, Gabi was voted "most likely to become famous."

She won't.

Unless you count "famous for always being late to school", which really isn't that great when you are the 3rd-grade teacher >>

12/12
Thank you for understanding. Thank you for supporting our art.
The discord server will stay frozen for now.
All updates from now on will be on this Twitter account.

11/12
We are going to use our time and resources to do ART. Tell STORIES. Think about what's good for the PROJECT. And mostly ‚Äì just be honest with ourselves. We can't run both an NFT project AND a discord server.

So we‚Äôre going with the project.

10/12
We are no security experts, nor we are experienced community managers or a big-budget studio, and that is OK. 
We are artists. And this is an ART project. With really GOOD art. We just needed that hack-break to remind ourselves of that.

9/12
well‚Ä¶ that just means you don't sleep. Which is, again, not beneficial for the project.
Discord is scary. It sometimes feels like the only reason projects are taking this risk is because ‚Äúeverybody else does‚Äù. Like all other aspects of life - that‚Äôs not a good enough reason

8/12
Now, add to that the constant fear of being hacked. If you are a big-budget project and can afford a trusted team to be on the lookout 24/7, maybe you can take the risk, but when you are a small project, and you know that someone can hack the server while you are asleep‚Ä¶

7/12
That ‚Äúunhappy‚Äù feeling, no matter how misleading, can make the founder question the project‚Äôs plans. You find yourself just wanting to please the ‚Äúunhappys‚Äù. Is this what's best for the project and the rest of the holders? Many times, it isn‚Äôt.

6/12
It's easy to forget, once you are sucked in, that "everyone" isn't really "everyone". There are over 3000 holders in our project. There are a few dozen active discord members. There are maybe 10 that are unhappy. But that‚Äôs enough to make you feel like ‚Äúeveryone‚Äôs unhappy‚Äù.

5/12
As a no-budget free mint project, it is up to us, the founders, to keep the discord channel up and running. From daily GMs to finding the right GIF, to chasing new announcements and updates, answering every question, and responding to every FUD, just to keep everyone happy.

4/12
Honestly, it was the first time we had a chance to catch our breath since this journey began two weeks ago. We are now realizing that all this time we weren't managing an NFT project. We were operating a Discord channel. And those are two very different things.

3/12
We decided to deactivate our discord channel until an admin can make sure it is safe. For the past 24 hours, we have become a no-discord project. Those hours have been the most creative and productive we've had since mint.

2/12
Fortunately, that post was deleted after less than a minute, thanks to a quick reaction from one of our team members. Sadly, 2 of our community members had already clicked the link and had their wallets compromised.
